NOTES: The .ijm file here is a macro to batch process multiple z-stacks to subtract background from before VESNA analysis. It will take in an input folder where the raw z-stacks are and an output folder where the background subtracted z-stacks will be placed and renamed with suffix '-SB'. A log window will update you on progress in Fiji
Installation:
1. go to the macro folder in your Fiji folder
2. Drop SubtractBG_batch.ijm into the macro folder
3. Open Fiji, then Plugins>Macro>Install and select the .ijm file
4. Open Plugins>Macro and SubtractBG_batch should appear to click on
5. Follow the prompts to select the input and output folders

This macro is meant to be used BEFORE VESNA processing





The VESNA_summarise_plots.py file is a python script to be used AFTER VESNA processing
VESNA will produce multiple .csv files in the specified output folder after it operates. This script will take in this output folder path (full path) and create a summary to automatically calculate Length Density, Branchpoint Density, Endpoint-to-Branchpoint Ratio and Median Tortuosity.
